          <p>England offers exceptional stargazing opportunities across numerous certified Dark Sky Parks and reserves. Despite its reputation for cloudy weather, England's countryside provides access to pristine dark skies, particularly in Northumberland (gold-tier International Dark Sky Park), Exmoor (Europe's darkest recorded skies), and the South Downs (accessible from London). The best viewing period is October through February, with autumn offering the clearest conditions and winter providing the longest nights.</p>
