            </ul>
          </div>

          <p>The key challenge for English stargazing is weather, not darkness. England's maritime climate brings frequent cloud cover, making clear nights precious. However, modern weather forecasting and astronomy apps allow you to track high-pressure systems and plan observations around clear conditions. Autumn (September-November) typically provides the best balance of clear skies and reasonable temperatures.</p>
